name: r-odbc
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.3.3" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-odbc
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/odbc_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/odbc/odbc_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 8a3fbe3171388b28027da6a7f6c094039c5073ab2c769bd2c57a8684afbeb6a8

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}grep              # [win]
    - {{ posix }}autoconf
    - {{ posix }}automake          # [not win]
    - {{ posix }}automake-wrapper  # [win]
    - {{ posix }}pkg-config
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-bh
    - r-dbi >=1.0.0
    - r-rcpp >=0.12.11
    - r-bit64
    - r-blob >=1.2.0
    - r-hms
    - r-rlang
    - unixodbc  # [unix]
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    # BH is the header-only part of Boost and thus a compile-time requirement only
    # - r-bh
    - r-dbi >=1.0.0
    - r-rcpp >=0.12.11
    - r-bit64
    - r-blob >=1.2.0
    - r-hms
    - r-rlang
    - unixodbc  # [unix]

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('odbc')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('odbc')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/r-dbi/odbc
  license: MIT
  summary: A DBI-compatible interface to ODBC databases.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - xhochy

# Package: odbc
# Title: Connect to ODBC Compatible Databases (using the DBI Interface)
# Version: 1.1.6

# Description: A DBI-compatible interface to ODBC databases.
